NHL ENTRY DRAFT
June 27, 1998
Christian Backman
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT








Q.  Did you have any idea -- (inaudible)

CHRISTIAN BACKMAN:  Yeah, a little bit.  I know they were interested in me.


Q.  What do you know about the team?

CHRISTIAN BACKMAN:  I know they had a great season this year.


Q.  (inaudible)

CHRISTIAN BACKMAN:  Yeah, I have done that sometimes before and I think the game is faster and it is more physical play and you have to be tougher.


Q.  (inaudible)

CHRISTIAN BACKMAN:  It is more things going on all the time.  You get more chances to score goals.  I like it.


Q.  (inaudible)

CHRISTIAN BACKMAN:  I am offensive/defenseman, like to carry the puck a lot and I am a good powerplay player, with a good hockey sense, read the play.


Q.  (inaudible)

CHRISTIAN BACKMAN:  Nicholas Lidstrom is my favorite player.


Q.  What do you think of the chances of playing --

CHRISTIAN BACKMAN:  When I make the NHL, hopefully in some years, I hope he will still be there and that will be a great opportunity for me.  I think I need some more years back in Sweden first to improve my physical play and maybe three to five years I will be ready.


End of FastScripts...

END_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT